headline: WM Q2 Deep Dive: Strong Volumes, Synergy Capture, and Technology Investments Drive Growth
summary: Waste management services provider Waste Management (NYSE:WM) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 19% year on year to $6.43 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $25.38 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.92 per share was 1.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
